      • getNode

        public CompositeElement getNode()
        Description copied from class: StubBasedPsiElementBase
        Ensures this element is AST-based. This is an expensive operation that might take significant time and allocate lots of objects, so it should be to be avoided if possible.
        Specified by:
        getNode in interface PsiElement
        Overrides:
        getNode in class StubBasedPsiElementBase<PsiParameterStub>
        Returns:
        an AST node corresponding to this element. If the element is currently operating via stubs, this causes AST to be loaded for the whole file and all stub-based PSI elements in this file (including the current one) to be switched from stub to AST. So, after this call StubBasedPsiElementBase.getStub() will return null.
